It is understood that taxi drivers and operators are unhappy about the delay in upgrading taxi ranks in the area. JOHANNESBURG - Several roads in Vereeniging have been blocked off to traffic due to a taxi strike. It is understood that taxi drivers and operators are unhappy about the delay in upgrading taxi ranks in the area. A motorist says that the whole area is on lockdown. "I'm trying to get to business and none of the businesses seem to be open. They have a WhatsApp group saying that they are closed today." In the Vereeniging CBD several roads are closed off to traffic due to a taxi strike #VAALTraffic pic.twitter.com/8L48S5MmIo 